# Next expansion roadmap

When adding Proxmox MCP tools or deciding “what’s next”:

1. Read `.cursor/research/next-expansion.md` (Phase D QOL vs Phase C heavy).
2. Prefer Phase D agent-friction fixes (`wait_for_task`, richer create_vm/lxc) over Phase C unless the user asks for SDN write / Ceph / cluster join.
3. Capture new API quirks in `.cursor/research/changelog-notes.md` and lasting decisions in `decisions.md`.
4. Follow `api-coverage.mdc` + `keep-docs-aligned.mdc` for inventory/docs lockstep.
